# ArkVault — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
ArkVault is a native HarmonyOS NEXT password manager built with ArkTS + ArkUI.

## Language & Framework
- Use ArkTS strict mode (NOT TypeScript)
- ArkTS forbids: `any`, `unknown`, dynamic object layout, most destructuring
- All types must be explicitly declared — no implicit `any`
- Use `T[]` not `Array<T>` for array types
- Use `Record<string, Object>` instead of plain `{}` for maps
- Strings use single quotes: `'hello'`
- Indentation: 2 spaces, no tabs
- Max line width: 120 characters
- One variable declaration per statement (no `let a = 1, b = 2`)

## Naming Conventions
- Classes/enums/namespaces: UpperCamelCase (`PasswordEntry`, `UserType`)
- Variables/methods/params: lowerCamelCase (`findUser`, `isLoading`)
- Constants/enum values: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_RETRY_COUNT`, `TEACHER`)
- Boolean vars: prefix with `is/has/can/should` (`isLocked`, `hasExpired`)
- Avoid negative booleans (`isNoError` → use `isError`)

## Security Rules (CRITICAL for password manager)
- Master password must NEVER be stored or logged in plaintext
- All sensitive data MUST go through Asset Store Kit — never use Preferences or plain files
- Encryption keys MUST use Universal Keystore Kit (hardware-backed), never soft-store
- Never use `console.log` / `console.info` to output passwords, keys, or tokens
- Clipboard must auto-clear after 30 seconds
- PBKDF2 iterations ≥ 600,000 for key derivation
- Use AES-256-GCM (not CBC) for symmetric encryption

## Architecture
- Layered: UI (pages/components) → Service Layer → Data Layer (models/DAO)
- Crypto operations live in `crypto/` module — UI never calls crypto APIs directly
- All DB access through DAO pattern — no raw SQL in business logic
- Import/export parsers are pure functions with no side effects

## HarmonyOS API Usage
- Reference `docs/skills/harmonyos-development.md` for ArkTS/ArkUI API patterns
- Reference `docs/arkts-coding-style-guide.md` for official coding conventions
- Use `@State`, `@Prop`, `@Link` for component state (V1 decorators)
- Use `@Observed` + `@ObjectLink` for nested object observation
- Prefer `LazyForEach` for large lists
- Navigation: use `NavPathStack` with named routes

## Code Style
- Arrow functions for event handlers
- Access modifiers on all class properties (`private`, `public`, `protected`)
- Use braces for all `if/for/while` blocks
- Operator at end of line when wrapping expressions
- `else`/`catch` on same line as closing brace: `} else {`
